## 1. Purpose
This policy ensures [COMPANY] maintains an accurate, complete inventory of its information assets, assigns ownership and classification, and manages each asset securely across its lifecycle. An accurate inventory is the foundation for risk assessment, access control, data protection, and incident response — you cannot protect what you do not know you have.

## 2. Scope
Applies to all information assets within the ISMS scope (`../governance/isms-scope-statement.md.template`), including but not limited to: cloud infrastructure and services ([AWS] accounts, compute, storage, databases), the [Snowflake] data warehouse, the [GitHub] organization and CI/CD pipeline, SaaS applications, endpoints (laptops/mobile), data stores containing PHI, software/code, and supporting documentation. Assets owned by vendors are governed jointly with `../vendor/third-party-risk-management-policy.md.template`.

## 3. Policy
1. [COMPANY] **shall** maintain an inventory of all in-scope information assets, recorded in [the asset inventory / CMDB / AWS Config + tagging] as the system of record.
2. Every asset **shall** have a named **owner** accountable for its protection, classification, and lifecycle.
3. Every asset **shall** be assigned a **classification** consistent with `data-classification-and-handling.md.template`, reflecting the most sensitive data it stores or processes (PHI-bearing assets are Restricted).
4. The inventory **shall** be reviewed and reconciled at least [quarterly] and updated upon asset acquisition, change, or decommission.
5. Cloud assets **shall** be discoverable and tagged (e.g., [AWS] resource tags for owner, environment, data classification) to enable automated inventory and policy enforcement.
6. Assets **shall** be managed across the lifecycle per §6, including secure provisioning, maintenance, and decommissioning/disposal per `data-retention-and-disposal.md.template`.
7. Removal of an asset from service **shall** ensure data is sanitized or destroyed before disposal or reassignment.
8. The inventory **shall** support incident response and risk assessment by identifying which assets hold PHI and their dependencies.

## 4. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [Security Officer / CISO] | Owns this policy; oversees the inventory; verifies classification accuracy. |
| [IT / Platform Team] | Maintains the inventory and tagging; performs reconciliation. |
| Asset Owners | Accountable for assigned assets: classification, access, lifecycle, decommission. |
| All Workforce | Use only authorized, inventoried assets; report unmanaged or lost assets. |

See `../governance/roles-and-responsibilities.md.template`.

