## 6. Asset Lifecycle
| Phase | Requirements |
|---|---|
| **Acquire / Provision** | Inventory the asset, assign owner and classification, apply baseline hardening and tagging. |
| **Operate / Maintain** | Patch, monitor, control access (`../access/access-control-policy.md.template`), keep inventory current. |
| **Change** | Significant changes follow `../operations/change-management-policy.md.template` and may trigger reassessment. |
| **Decommission / Dispose** | Sanitize or destroy data per `data-retention-and-disposal.md.template`; revoke access; remove from inventory with record. |

## 7. Exceptions
Exceptions to this policy require documented risk acceptance per `../governance/exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by [Security Officer], time-bound, and recorded in the exceptions log.

## 8. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
The [Security Officer] verifies inventory completeness and classification accuracy through periodic reconciliation and audit. Untagged or unmanaged assets are remediated. Adherence is mandatory; violations are handled per `../people/hr-security-policy.md.template`.

